Hi, we were debugging our code when we suddenly got strange errors. What happened on deploy was that after getting the normal startup messages in green, we get a “no code” error in the DS log. However, the DS indicator for robot code is green, and it lets me enable the code. I deployed test code that reads our analog encoder positions and spins a motor (it’s random code for testing something specific, and I never comment out old lines). The analog encoders were reporting values normally, but the motor (Falcon 500) did not spin. It’s spun in the past. After the no code error we get a message saying Phoenix has initialized (normal since we use Talon FX motors). Is there any way to fix it? Rebooting the robot didn’t help.

EDIT: Reimaging the RIO and redeploying code didn’t work.

We checked the firmware; it was up to date. After running a test program on another computer it worked without issues. It seems to be an issue with the YAGSL configuration now. An old configuration that still used the phoenix library but had incorrect offsets and inverse ran without error. It seems to be a configuration error. I regenerated the config files but I didn’t get the chance to test them. I’ll have to wait until Monday.
